        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 529 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pompton Lakes, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Paterson, Stamford, Wayne, New City, Ossining, Ridgewood, Monsey,
Nanuet, Ramsey, Ringwood, Haverstraw, Tarrytown, Pompton Lakes, Mount
Kisco, and Suffern.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
